main event: On January 30, 1965, a light craft was observed for 2 hours in La Selva Beach, California, during which contact was made with the ship.
interesting points: The witness reported entering the ship and experiencing a ride for 2 hours., The report states that there was no physical evidence or photographs., Witness described the craft as having a highly polished smooth silver surface., The craft was observed at low altitude and was seen by at least 10 other people., Several sketches were made by the witnesses during the observation.
witness description: The primary witness appears to be a civilian, possibly with a military background, given the mention of being engaged in the Civil Air Patrol and having a high school education.
